OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773765945
OL,3,CWoman who wrote book on grief after
OL,4,Chusband's death found guilty of his
OL,5,Cmurder
OL,7,FRichins was also convicted of other
OL,8,Ffelonies, including attempted murder
OL,9,Ffor trying to poison her husband weeks
OL,10,Fearlier on Valentine's Day with a
OL,11,Ffentanyl-laced sandwich that made him
OL,12,Fblack out.
OL,14,FThe aggravated murder charge alone
OL,15,Fcarries a sentence of 25 years to life
OL,16,Fin prison.
OL,18,F"Honestly, I feel like we're all in
OL,19,Fshock. It's been a long time coming,"
OL,20,Fsaid Eric Richins' sister, Amy Richins.
OL,26,@zD@AOU{D@eO]
